    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - SLAVE VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="6">
        <title>SLAVE VALVE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hose between the slave valve and the LO range
                port in the range cylinder housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302916">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302916" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302916" filename="../figg13/G1302916.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Disconnect Air Hose Between Slave Valve and LO Range Port</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hose between the slave valve and the HI range
                port in the range cylinder cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302917">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302917" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302917" filename="../figg13/G1302917.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Disconnect Air Hose Between Slave Valve and HI Range Port</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four retaining bolts and the slave valve from transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302918">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302918" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302918" filename="../figg13/G1302918.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Retaining Bolts and Slave Valve</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the hat-type alignment sleeve from the bore in the slave valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302919">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302919" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302919" filename="../figg13/G1302919.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove Alignment Sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spring and plunger pin from the transmission case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302920">Figure 20</hotlnk>). Remove the slave valve gasket.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302920" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302920" filename="../figg13/G1302920.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Spring and Plunger Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the air line fittings from the slave valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302921">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302921" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302921" filename="../figg13/G1302921.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Remove Air Line Fittings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For disassembly and reassembly, refer to piston-type
                    <hotlnk document="s13029_X1302904.xml" xrefid="x1302904">Slave Valve Assembly</hotlnk>
                    ONLY.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
